This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically optical flow estimation, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for this task, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a synthetic dataset, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.RO (Robotics).
